The code has been updated to address the overlapping y-axis labels in the Random Forest Permutation Importances plot (Image 4). 
Instead of wrapping the text (which caused vertical overlap due to the number of bars), the predictor names are now strictly truncated to a maximum of 60 characters, appending an ellipsis ("...") if they exceed this length. This ensures each label occupies only a single line, preventing vertical overlap. Additionally, the figure size has been adjusted, and `plt.tight_layout()` is used to ensure the left margin accommodates the truncated labels properly.

